# Organization Development Guidelines (v1.0.0)

Adapted for the **save-app** Expo / TypeScript client. Backend Python rules from the org doc are mapped to the equivalent tooling in this repo.

## Git & Version Control

### Branch Naming

```
[type]/[ticket-id]-[short-description]
```

| Type | Purpose | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| `feature/` | New features | `feature/PROJ-123-user-authentication` |
| `bugfix/` | Non-prod bug fixes | `bugfix/PROJ-456-fix-login-error` |
| `hotfix/` | Urgent production fixes | `hotfix/PROJ-789-payment-gateway-crash` |
| `chore/` | Maintenance, deps, docs | `chore/PROJ-100-update-readme` |

Workflow: pull latest from `main` Ôćĺ create branch Ôćĺ open Draft PR early Ôćĺ mark Ready for Review when done.

### Commit Messages (Conventional Commits)

```
<type>(<scope>): <short summary>

[optional body]
```

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`

Example: `feat(auth): add JWT token refresh on 401`

## Code Style & Quality (TypeScript)

| Org standard (Python) | This project |
|-----------------------|------------|
| Ruff / Black | `npm run lint` (ESLint + expo lint) |
| Type hints | TypeScript `strict` ÔÇö no `any` |
| Google docstrings | JSDoc only for non-obvious public APIs |
| Import order | external Ôćĺ `@/` Ôćĺ relative |

Before committing:

```bash
npm run lint
npm run typecheck
npm test
```

See also: `core-standards.mdc`, `typescript-quality.mdc`.

## API Design & Versioning

- RESTful nouns: `/users`, not `/getUsers`
- Correct HTTP methods: GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE
- URI versioning: `/api/v1/[resource]` ÔÇö base URL in `src/constants/api.ts`
- Route paths only in `src/api/routes/` ÔÇö never hardcode in services/hooks/components
- Breaking changes Ôćĺ new major API version; non-breaking Ôćĺ stay on current version

Layer order: `routes` Ôćĺ `services` Ôćĺ `hooks` Ôćĺ `components`

## Testing Requirements (Frontend)

API contract and endpoint tests belong to the **backend** repo ÔÇö do not duplicate them here.

Frontend tests cover:

- UI components (`src/components/`)
- Hooks and client logic (`src/hooks/`)
- Pure helpers/utils (`src/utils/`)
- Design tokens when logic exists (`src/constants/` ÔÇö excluding `api.ts`)

Rules:

- Every new feature or bug fix should include frontend unit/component tests when applicable
- Target **80% coverage** on new/changed frontend code (hooks, components, utils)
- Run locally before push: `npm test`
- Component tests: `@testing-library/react-native`
- Pure logic: Jest without rendering

Test files: `**/__tests__/*.{test,spec}.{ts,tsx}` or `*-test.{ts,tsx}`

## Definition of Done

A task is **Done** only when:

1. `npm run lint` passes
2. `npm run typecheck` passes
3. `npm test` passes (add frontend tests when the change warrants them)
4. App runs without errors in dev
5. PR reviewed and approved (team process)
6. CI pipeline passes
7. README / docs updated when applicable
8. Loading, error, and empty states handled (UI tasks)

See `production-checklist.mdc` for UI/UX delivery criteria.
